flowRoot.flowPara: Fig. A2 - Logged in home page

Category selection - selecting a category advances user to the respective "category screen" (fig. B1) if no selection was made on that day for that category. If a selection was made, the user advances to the respective "summary screen" (fig. F1).
Confirm - advances user to the "pending confirmation screen" (fig. H1)
App Settings - advances user to the "app settings screen" (fig. G1)
Strategy change button - lets the user change the strategy that will be used to select selected participants. Brings user to the "strategy select" screen (fig. C1)
"More" and "Fewer" buttons - increments/decrements the number of participants to be selected by Whose Turn

Participant Selection - A list of users and recently selected guests, as well as a "Guest" option that allows selection of guests that do not appear on the list/not-recently selected guests. Clicking on a user/guest will toggle whether they are participating.
Whose Turn? button - Triggers the selection process and brings user to the "selection result screen" (fig. E1)
Lists a set of available strategies - strategies that dictate the algorithm that will be used in the selection process

Each strategy may have a set of corresponding options tied to that strategy. Considering the small number of strategies available, it is suggested that the options be listed below the activation button for each strategy (below each strategy's description).
Fig. B1a - Category Screen scrolled downward
This is Fig. B1 with the main content scrolled. The "Guest" button is shown.
Clicking the "Guest" button advances the user to the "guest select screen" (fig. D1)
Allows the user to select a guest - a person that does not have an account on the system.
Textbox - Enter text to perform a search for an existing guest, or enter the guest's complete name
Guest participant selection - lists the guests that match the search (or all guests if no matches are made).
Similar to "Participant selection" of fig. B1, active selections are highlighted and may be toggled with a click.
Typing "Gordon" in the text box advances the user to Fig. D1a
Fig. D1a - Guest Select Screen with "Gordon" entered into the textbox

Here, a partial-match/"smart" search has filtered guests down to three options. The "Guest participant selection" list also shows a "Select new guest" option - in case the user has typed the complete name of the guest.
If the user wanted to select "Gordon Freeman", they would see that he is not in the list and enter his last name, bringing the user to Fig. D1b
Fig. D1b - Guest Select Screen with "Gordon Freeman" entered into the textbox

Here, the user likely wants to select "Gordon Freeman" as a guest. Clicking "Select new guest" will automatically create a new guest named appropriately and add the guest to the participants pool (and to the "Participant selection" list in Fig. B1)
Shows the result of the selection process. If multiple persons were selected, they would all be shown on the same page with smaller icons.
Clicking the "cancel and return" button will undo any changes to appropriate entities and return the user to the category screen.
Clicking the "summary" button brings the user to the "summary screen" - but makes no changes to any entities - the user may navigate away from the page at this point.
Note that typical usage of the app consists of interaction with only fig. A2 and fig. B1. No interaction with fig. E1 is necessary (other than reading the result).
Shows lists of selected participants and passive participnats (users/guests that participated in the category that day of whom weren't selected)

Also shows the strategy used, who submitted the selection request, and what fraction of applicable participants verified the submittal (applicable participants include passive participants who are not guests).

A point of contention: should the original submitter be able to cancel the turn if others have verified the "whose turn"? "Cancel" brings the user to fig. F1a. This screen is different for applicable participants (see fig. F1z).
Fig. F1a - Summary screen cancel verification prompt
Clicking "No" preserves state and returns the user to the "summary screen" (fig. F1).
Clicking "Yes" cancels the "Whose Turn" and returns the user to the "Category Screen" (fig. B1).
Here, the user can sign in to Whose Turn and/or create an account. Design of the actual login and register pages depends upon how the federated login system will work.
This screen is not displayed if the user's login is saved - in which case, the user is presented with fig. A2.
Lets the user change global settings, manage categories, manage users, and log out.

flowRoot.flowPara: Displays a list of "whose turn"s the user needs to confirm or dispute.
When a "whose turn" is viewed, the user is not the person who submitted, and the user has not confirmed/disputed a "whose turn", they are presented with confirm and dispute buttons.
